All the Meiweiyuan pepper sauce products in China must be removed from the shelves, said AQSIQ in a circular, Friday.
Sudan I is a red dye used for coloring solvents, oils waxes, petrol and shoe and floor polishes.
China launched a food safety inspection when Sudan I was detected in a pepper sauce produced by a subsidiary of American company Heinz, Heinz-Meiweiyuan Food Co., Ltd. in southern China's Guangzhou city earlier this month.
The dye, which was at the center of a European health scare, was found in both KFC and Heinz products.
